{"word":"ἄσκησις","slug":"ἄσκησις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄσκησις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀσκέω'><el>ἀσκέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>exercise, practice, training</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>exercises</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἄσκ. τινος</el> <i>practice of</i> or <i>in</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>generally, <i>a mode of life, profession, art</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}